The paper discusses a method for summarization of biomedical text documents using graph-based modelling and centrality measures. This falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the focus is on text summarization, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely categories.
